  "time_ut": 1661169067,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u2018\u201822 \u0da2\u0db1\u0dad\u0dcf \u0db4\u0dbb\u0db8\u0dcf\u0db0\u0dd2\u0db4\u0dad\u0dca\u200d\u0dba\u0dba\u0da7 \u0dc4\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dd2\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dca\u2018\u2018",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "\"22 Damage to People's Sovereignty\"",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "President's Counsel Mr. Manoharada Silva told the Supreme Court today (22) that the 22nd Constitutional Amendment Bill will curtail the powers of the Executive President and thereby harm the sovereignty of the people.",
        "09 petitions filed before the Supreme Court by nine persons including Dr. Gunadasa Amarasekara, stating that certain clauses of the 22nd Constitution Amendment Bill are contrary to the Constitution, requesting to issue an order to pass it by a special number of members and a referendum, were heard before the Supreme Court today (22). These facts were presented at the time.",
        "President's lawyer Manohara de Silva, who appeared before the Supreme Court on behalf of one of the petitioners, Colonel Sumeda Amarasinghe, said so.",
        "These petitions were taken into consideration today (22) before a Supreme Court bench consisting of Chief Justice Jayantha Jayasuriya, Mr. Buwaneka Aluvihare and Mr. Arjuna Obeysekera.",
        "Dr. Gunadasa Amarasekara, Colonel Sumeda Amarasinghe, General Secretary of the Praideh Peramuna Lawyer Nagananda Kodithuvakku, Lawyer Nuvan Bellantudawe and Sabaragamu University Senior Lecturer H. S. Nine people including Mr. Kumar have filed these petitions before the Supreme Court and the Attorney General has been named as the respondent."
      ],
